==Abstract==

This IIP describes opt-in Replace-by-Fee (RBF) signaling, allowing unconfirmed transactions to be replaced with higher-fee versions. It implements BIP 125 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

RBF provides:
* Fee bumping when transactions are stuck
* Transaction cancellation (send to self with higher fee)
* Better fee estimation (start low, bump if needed)

==Specification==

===Signaling===

A transaction signals RBF replaceability if any input has:
<pre>
nSequence < 0xffffffff - 1  (i.e., nSequence < 0xfffffffe)
</pre>

===Replacement Rules===

A replacement transaction must:

# '''Signal RBF''': Original transaction must have signaled
# '''Spend same inputs''': Must spend at least one of the same inputs
# '''Higher fee''': Must pay strictly higher total fee
# '''Higher fee rate''': Must pay higher fee rate than original
# '''Pay for bandwidth''': Additional fee must cover replacement tx size at min relay fee
# '''Limited descendants''': Original can have at most 100 descendants

===Fee Calculation===

<pre>
new_fee > old_fee
new_fee >= old_fee + (new_size * min_relay_fee_rate)
</pre>

===Mempool Behavior===

When a valid replacement arrives:
# Remove original transaction and all descendants
# Add replacement transaction
# Re-evaluate dependent transactions

===Wallet Implementation===

Wallets supporting RBF SHOULD:
* Set nSequence = 0xfffffffd for RBF-enabled inputs
* Display RBF status in transaction history
* Provide "Bump Fee" functionality

